00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:34,000
All right, let's go.

302
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:46,000
You have to contact them somehow.

304
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:08,000
Well, it was nice knowing him.

305
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:09,000
Think I could have his computer?

309
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:19,000
Fenton's got game!

310
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,000
Who knew?

311
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:28,000
There's a ghost in here.

312
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:30,000
I can feel it in my boots.

313
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:32,000
And I'm not leaving this campus

314
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:35,000
till these gloves grab some ghost.

315
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,000
A ghost?

316
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:41,000
That can't be right.

318
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,000
Looks like we'll be sticking up the school all night.

319
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:45,000
Don't wait up.

320
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:48,000
In that case, I need to use the little ghost on his room.

321
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,000
Hold these gloves, son.

322
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:52,000
Where I'm going, there's no need for that much power.

323
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,000
Party at Fenton's house!

324
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:58,000
Yay!

325
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,000
Hot dog!

326
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,000
Where does he live?

327
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:02,000
It's your house, bonehead.

328
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:05,000
Is he a lairs of what?

329
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,000
Free soda, a touchdown, and the opportunity

330
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,000
to trash a classmate's living room.

331
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:13,000
How easily the letter jacket and pom-pom set is swayed.

332
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:14,000
I don't know.

333
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,000
Denny seems a little off.

334
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:20,000
Although, the residual popularity

335
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:22,000
effect could work to our advantage.

336
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:25,000
Oh, Kwan, you simply must wear one of these

337
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:27,000
Save the Frogs badges.

338
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:29,000
It's all the rage.

339
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:30,000
I don't know.

340
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,000
Hey, boss badge.

341
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:34,000
Can I have one?

342
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:36,000
Hey, I want one.

343
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,000
Me too.

344
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:40,000
I can wear it with my old army lime green baby tea.

345
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:41,000
Give me one, yo.

346
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,000
I started this trend.

347
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:44,000
Hang on, folks.

348
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:47,000
Plenty more in my locker where that one came from.

349
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:54,000
Sam, Tucker in here.

350
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:55,000
Windexter?

351
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:57,000
No, it's me, Denny.

352
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:59,000
Windexter took over my body and sent me

353
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,000
into this bizarro spirit world.

354
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,000
Prove it.

355
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,000
In second grade, Tucker threw up in your lunchbox,

356
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,000
but he told you Ricky Marsh did it.

357
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:08,000
What?

358
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:10,000
I kicked him off the monkey bars for that.

359
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:12,000
It was you?

360
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:13,000
Denny?

361
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:16,000
The mirror acts as some kind of portal,

362
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:18,000
but I can't face through it.

363
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:20,000
Serves me right.

364
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:22,000
I'm only in here because I was acting like a bully.

365
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:24,000
Now I'm in here and I'm going to get bullied

366
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,000
for the rest of eternity.

367
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:27,000
You might not be able to get out,

368
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:30,000
but that doesn't mean Poindexter can't get back in.

369
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:34,000
I doubt he's in a big hurry to go back where he came from.

370
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:36,000
I know how to get him in here.

371
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:38,000
Here's what you need to do.

372
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:40,000
Denny, come quick.

373
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:43,000
A bully is shoving a poor, defenseless nerd

374
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:45,000
inside his own locker.

375
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,000
Tucker, I'll save you.

376
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:53,000
Hey, there's no nerd getting shoved inside his locker.

377
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,000
There is now.

378
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,000
No!

379
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:04,000
You've had your fun.

380
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:07,000
Now I want my body and my life back.

381
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,000
Forget you, bully.

382
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:10,000
You're not going anywhere.

383
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:14,000
No!

384
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:20,000
Aha! I'm doing it!

385
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:24,000
Huh? You may have my powers,

386
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,000
but you sure don't know how to use them?

387
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:27,000
Of course, I don't know how to use them,

388
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,000
but at least I know how not to use them better than you do.

389
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:30,000
What?

390
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:33,000
You wouldn't hit a guy with glasses.

391
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:36,000
You couldn't hit a guy with glasses.

392
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:39,000
In fact, you couldn't hit the broad side of a barn.

393
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:41,000
Hold still.

394
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:45,000
But I think you're going to kill him.

395
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:50,000
Fight, fight, fight, fight, fight, fight, fight, fight, fight.

396
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:53,000
Hey, get a load of poi, Dexter.

397
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,000
He's fighting the half-a.

398
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:59,000
Yeah, look at him stand up to that weird head, ghost bully.

399
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:00,000
I'm not a bully!

400
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:05,000
Now, if you don't mind, I'm going to live it up some more

401
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:07,000
in your body.

402
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,000
What?

403
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:15,000
One false move, and I smash your door back to my world.

404
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:16,000
You wouldn't.

405
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:18,000
You'd strand us both here.

406
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,000
Try me.

407
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,000
I've got a better idea.

408
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:25,000
I can make you.

409
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:27,000
With your powers, I can make you do anything.

410
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:34,000
That's what I was hoping you'd do.

411
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:35,000
You!

412
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,000
Oh, yeah!

413
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:41,000
Huh?

414
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:43,000
No!

415
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:50,000
I'll get out of here, Buster Brown.

416
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:53,000
And when I do, you better watch it.

417
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:55,000
Hey, nerd.

418
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,000
Nice job standing up to the half-a.

419
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:59,000
Who'd have thought you had it, did you?

420
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:02,000
You want to grab an egg cream?

421
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:05,000
Of course I could hang it for a little bit.

422
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:07,000
Hey, the heck with the egg cream.

423
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,000
Who's up for a diet soda?

424
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:10,000
Whatever that is.

425
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,000
Oh!

426
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:18,000
No, come back!

427
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:20,000
Oh, dear, whatever we do.

428
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,000
Could win, Danny?

429
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:22,000
Yeah.

430
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:24,000
But how do we know you're really Danny?

431
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:26,000
Because I used my powers for the wrong reason

432
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:29,000
and became exactly the kind of person I hate.

433
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:31,000
It got me into a load of trouble,

434
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:33,000
and I'm not going to do that again.

435
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:35,000
Now that's the Danny I remember.

436
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:38,000
Just one more thing to do.

437
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:43,000
Fenton, that school property.

438
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:46,000
I can explain.

439
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:48,000
Actually, I really can't.

440
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:51,000
I'm holding you responsible for this.

441
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:53,000
I'm the escaped frogs.

442
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:56,000
But seeing how outstanding students like Dash Baxter

443
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:58,000
have made their opinions known,

444
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:01,000
I'm willing to overlook the frogs.

445
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:04,000
Miss Manson, you could learn a thing or two from them

446
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:06,000
about activism.

447
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:09,000
Still, that leaves the matter of your locker.

448
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:12,000
I'm going to have to assign you a new one.

449
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:20,000
Hanging with band geeks, Fenton?

450
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:23,000
No amount of free soda is going to fix that.

451
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:25,000
Hi, I'm Lyle.

452
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:28,000
Wanna help me clean my spit mouth?

453
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:32,000
My 15 minutes of popularity is up,

454
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:34,000
and I wasn't even here for it.

455
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:37,000
Yeah, but at least it wasn't a total loss.

456
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:40,000
Looks like this baby's going to get some use after all.

457
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:46,000
I am no longer the box ghost.

458
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:50,000
I am now the mechanical frog ghost.

459
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:57,000
I changed my mind.

460
00:22:57,000 --> 00:23:00,000
I am once again the box ghost

461
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:04,000
who will have nothing to do with mechanical amphibians.

462
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:06,000
Beware!

463
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:09,000
Now there's a guy who knows exactly who he is.

464
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,000
You're it.

